(firstQuint)Effectiveness of Clozapine Versus Olanzapine for Treatment-resistant Schizophrenia.

 This is a two-year open-label, randomized trial of the comparative effectiveness of clozapine versus olanzapine in patients with treatment refractory schizophrenia.

 The objective is to determine whether in a naturalistic setting olanzapine is a logical treatment choice (before using the more toxic clozapine) for some treatment refractory patients.

